-- Japan Orders Military to Destroy Any North Korea Rocket Debris
-- B y   T a k a s h i   H i r o k a w a
-- 2012-12-07T01:08:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-07/japan-orders-military-to-destroy-any-north-korea-rocket-debris.html
Japan  ordered its defense forces to
intercept and destroy any debris from North Korea’s planned
rocket launch this month that may fall in the country’s
territory.  Defense Minister Satoshi Morimoto gave the order this
morning, Chief Cabinet Secretary Osamu Fujimura told reporters
today in Tokyo. No part of the rocket is expected to hit Japan,
Fujimura said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Takashi Hirokawa in Tokyo at 
